name: Nashville Code User Group Leadership
body:
### Nashville Code User Group Leadership
Welcome to the meta user group for code focused user group leaders to meet, share initiatives, and in general support each other. We are open to any organizer of an initiative based in Nashville that focuses on growing, supporting and teaching the developer community. 

Currently we meet once a quarter with occasional one-off meetings in between scheduled as needed. To get on the mailing list for specifics please apply to the google group here: [NCUSGL](https://groups.google.com/forum/?fromgroups=#!forum/ncusgl)  

List of current groups/initiatives represented

[Cocoa Heads](http://www.cocoaheads.org/us/NashvilleTennessee/)

[The Code Collaborative](http://coop.nashvl.org)

[CoderFaire](http://coderfaire.com)

Google Mobile Development Group

[HackNashville](http://hacknashville.com)
**IRC #hacknashville**

[ID of Nashville](http://www.idofnashville.com)

[NashJS](http://nashjs.org)
**IRC #nashjs**

[Nashville DotNet](http://nashdotnet.org)

[Nashville Java](http://www.meetup.com/nashvillejug/)

Nashville AWS

[Nashville PHP](http://nashvillephp.org)
**IRC #nashvillephp**

[PyNash](http://pynash.org)
**IRC #pynash**

[SkyDogCon](http://skydogcon.com)

[Women's STEM Group](http://nashstem.com)

[Vim User Group](https://groups.google.com/forum/?fromgroups=#!forum/nashville-vim)
